=head1 DESCRIPTION

The proposed access control configuration for an Amazon RDS DB cluster
snapshot. You can propose a configuration for a new Amazon RDS DB
cluster snapshot or an Amazon RDS DB cluster snapshot that you own by
specifying the C<RdsDbClusterSnapshotAttributeValue> and optional KMS
encryption key. For more information, see
ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/APIReference/API_ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Attributes => L<Paws::AccessAnalyzer::RdsDbClusterSnapshotAttributesMap>

The names and values of manual DB cluster snapshot attributes. Manual
DB cluster snapshot attributes are used to authorize other Amazon Web
Services accounts to restore a manual DB cluster snapshot. The only
valid value for C<AttributeName> for the attribute map is C<restore>


=head2 KmsKeyId => Str

The KMS key identifier for an encrypted Amazon RDS DB cluster snapshot.
The KMS key identifier is the key ARN, key ID, alias ARN, or alias name
for the KMS key.

=over

=item *

If the configuration is for an existing Amazon RDS DB cluster snapshot
and you do not specify the C<kmsKeyId>, or you specify an empty string,
then the access preview uses the existing C<kmsKeyId> of the snapshot.

=item *

If the access preview is for a new resource and you do not specify the
specify the C<kmsKeyId>, then the access preview considers the snapshot
as unencrypted.

=back




